We reiterated our prior year’s recommendation with modifications, and Management agreed to require the OMA to:
Retrieve, as much as practicable, all documents of prior years’ records to determine the nature and composition of the book reconciling items;
Draw the necessary journal entries to take up in the books all valid reconciling items duly supported with proper documentation and furnish the AT with copies thereof;
Extend extra effort on initiating representations with the bank’s central office to obtain the details or copies of the unrecorded CMs and DMs and subsequently prepare the proper adjusting entries for the identified transactions; and
Ensure to prioritize the retrieval of supporting documents for the recording of the identified book reconciling items for the 14 bank accounts that were already closed to finally reflect the correct CIB balances at yearend.

We reiterated our prior year’s recommendation and Management agreed to:
Advise the Local Finance Committee and other officials concerned to regularly monitor the MGC’s cash position and immediately notify the LCE of any cash insufficiency noted;
Require the OMA and the MTO to ensure that monies held in trust are used solely for their intended purpose;
Ensure that expenditures incurred are only for projects, programs, and activities that are highly necessary and cannot be dispensed with; and
Adopt effective revenue-enhancing strategies and cost-cutting measures to eliminate the cash deficit/overdraft.

We recommended and Management agreed to:
Require the MGSO, in coordination with the concerned departments, to conduct complete physical inventory count of all inventories and prepare the RPCI semestrally based on the results of the actual count with complete details and description of the inventoried items;
Instruct the OMA and MGSO to: (i) analyze the deficiencies noted and reconcile their records; (ii) effect the necessary adjustments in the books of accounts, if warranted; and (iii) maintain complete and updated SCs and SLCs for each inventory item;
Instruct the MGSO to properly accomplish the SSMI by recording the inventory items in the aforesaid report once these have been actually distributed to the intended recipients; and
Remind the concerned departments to submit the pertinent documents to OMA and MGSO, immediately after the distribution of the inventory items, to facilitate timely preparation of SSMIs as a basis for recording corresponding expense accounts, and ensure to retain copies said documents for monitoring and recording purposes.

We recommended and Management agreed to:
Refrain from reporting PPAs as completed without verification on the actual status of the same from the recipient Barangays alongside its liquidation reports;
Require from the Barangay recipients their immediate compliance with the rules and regulations embodied in the MOA to ensure accountability, transparency, and strict safeguarding of government funds from any misappropriation or unnecessary use;
Consistently remind the MPDO, MBO, and MEO of the consistent monitoring of implementation of PPAs under the 20% DF and ensure the preparation and submission of complete and accurate project monitoring reports that are relevant in decision-making;
Adopt strategic measures on the implementation of the identified development PPAs for the attainment of the optimum utilization of the 20% DF and achieve the desired socio-economic development and environmental management outcomes of the MGC, essential in the realization of the constitutional objective of quality of life for all.

